Hello, I am Chin Wei.
I’m currently a MSc psychology researcher at the University of Hull, as part of the prestigious White Rose Doctoral Training Partnership (WRDTP).
Before this, I completed my Bachelor’s degree in Psychology at Nanyang Technological University, Singapore, where I was honoured the title NTU President Research Scholar for two consecutive years, thanks to my work in the Undergraduate Research Experience on Campus (URECA) programme.
I had the opportunity to lead two independent, year-long research projects under the guidance of faculty mentors, solidifying my love for all things research.
